            <div type="translation">
                <p>Brothers, glory and honor and peace to every man who works good.</p>
            </div>
            <div type="commentary">
                <p>Good condition. A cross with dots in the angles marks the beginning of the text. The words τιμή, εἰρήνη, ἐργαζομένῳ, as well as the conjuction καί and the article τῷ are misspelled. Two cross-like elements are placed at the very end of the text, a feature that we encounter in books and archival documents. The verse is taken from the Rom. 2:10.</p>
            </div>
